description.plain: Baby Tate (formerly Yung Baby Tate) is an artist and producer based out of Atlanta, GA. She first introduced herself to the music scene with ROYGBIV, an EP she released in 2015 under the name “Tate.” YBT is one of the most creative and versatile artists of our generation. Her talents range from singing, rapping, writing and producing in a plethora of genres. She’s the next big thing.

description.plain: I Am is a song off of Yung Baby Tate’s 2020 EP, After the Rain. The lyrics of the song preach messages of self-love and confidence, and it marks her first collaboration with Flo Milli. It has already racked up over 100,000 videos using the sound on the popular social media, TikTok.

songs.title: Hey, Mickey!

description.plain: Baby Tates interpolated Toni Basil’s 1979 hit “Hey Mickey” and updated it with new verses and a twist of Mickey being gay. Seven years after its release, the song went viral as a TikTok audio.
